info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 2:56PM EDT by NWS Miami
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Palm Beach County through 330 PM EDT... At 256 PM EDT, National Weather Service meteorologists were tracking strong thunderstorms capable of producing a funnel cloud along a line extending from North County Airport to near Wellington. Movement was east at 5 mph. HAZARD...Funnel clouds and winds in excess of 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Funnel clouds occasionally touch down and produce tornadoes or waterspouts. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... West Palm Beach, Wellington, Jupiter, Palm Beach Gardens, Riviera Beach, Tequesta, Greenacres, Royal Palm Beach, Haverhill, Loxahatchee NWR, Golden Lakes, North County Airport, Loxahatchee Groves, Lion Country Safari Park, Schall Circle, Royal Palm Estates, Lake Belvedere Estates, The Acreage, Lakeside Green and Philo Farms. FUNNEL CLOUD...POSSIBLE MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: These winds can down small tree limbs and branches, and blow around unsecured small objects. Seek shelter in a safe building until the storm passes. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
